The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Good Morning
      Hello It's Monday , June 21 , 2010                    
	Roads to avoid    Left Front supporters will meet at Netaji Indoor Stadium from Howrah, Sealdah and other parts of the city from 2pm for the 33rd anniversary of the Left Front government. The programme will continue till 5.30pm.    
	Theatre    Nehru Childrens Museum presents its seventh drama festival featuring Luxemberger Lakshmi at Academy of Fine Arts, 6.30pm.     
	Music    Concert to mark World Music Day at GD Birla Sabhagar, 6.30pm.    
	Exhibition    Furniturex, an exhibition at Calcutta Ice Skating Rink, 11am- 8pm.     
	Art watch    Summer Show 2010, an exhibition at CIMA Gallery, 3pm to 7pm.    Monsoon Melodies, an exhibition of terracotta works at Gallery 79, 4pm to 8pm.    Radha, paintings by Ananda Das, at Academy of Fine Arts, 3pm to 8pm.    Writing Visuals, art works at The Harrington Street Arts Centre, noon to 8pm.                                                                                                                                                  
